Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with formalising denotational semantics using logical relations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with denotational semantics of programming languages, specifically the simply typed lambda calculus extended with recursive types. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is relevant as the paper uses Guarded Dependent Type Theory to develop the denotational semantics. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with formalising denotational semantics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with semantics and proofs of properties of programming languages, which is relevant to software engineering.
